102 class ScriptObject
103 {
104  friend class ScriptMgr;
105 
106 public:
107  // Do not override this in scripts; it should be overridden by the various script type classes. It indicates
108  // whether or not this script type must be assigned in the database.
109  [[nodiscard]] virtual bool IsDatabaseBound() const { return false; }
110  [[nodiscard]] virtual bool isAfterLoadScript() const { return IsDatabaseBound(); }
111  virtual void checkValidity() { }
112 
113  [[nodiscard]] const std::string& GetName() const { return _name; }
114 
115 protected:
116  ScriptObject(const char* name)
117  : _name(std::string(name))
118  {
119  }
120 
121  virtual ~ScriptObject() = default;
122 
123 private:
124  const std::string _name;
125 };

151 class ServerScript : public ScriptObject
152 {
153 protected:
154  ServerScript(const char* name);
155 
156 public:
157  // Called when reactive socket I/O is started (WorldSocketMgr).
158  virtual void OnNetworkStart() { }
159 
160  // Called when reactive I/O is stopped.
161  virtual void OnNetworkStop() { }
162 
163  // Called when a remote socket establishes a connection to the server. Do not store the socket object.
164  virtual void OnSocketOpen(std::shared_ptr<WorldSocket> /*socket*/) { }
165 
166  // Called when a socket is closed. Do not store the socket object, and do not rely on the connection
167  // being open; it is not.
168  virtual void OnSocketClose(std::shared_ptr<WorldSocket> /*socket*/) { }
169 
170  // Called when a packet is sent to a client. The packet object is a copy of the original packet, so reading
171  // and modifying it is safe.
172  virtual void OnPacketSend(WorldSession* /*session*/, WorldPacket& /*packet*/) { }
173 
174  // Called when a (valid) packet is received by a client. The packet object is a copy of the original packet, so
175  // reading and modifying it is safe. Make sure to check WorldSession pointer before usage, it might be null in case of auth packets
176  virtual void OnPacketReceive(WorldSession* /*session*/, WorldPacket& /*packet*/) { }
177 };

257 template<class TMap> class MapScript : public UpdatableScript<TMap>
258 {
259  MapEntry const* _mapEntry;
260  uint32 _mapId;
261 
262 protected:
263  MapScript(uint32 mapId)
264  : _mapId(mapId)
265  {
266  }
267 
268 public:
269  void checkMap()
270  {
271  _mapEntry = sMapStore.LookupEntry(_mapId);
272 
273  if (!_mapEntry)
274  LOG_ERROR("maps.script", "Invalid MapScript for %u; no such map ID.", _mapId);
275  }
276 
277  // Gets the MapEntry structure associated with this script. Can return nullptr.
278  MapEntry const* GetEntry() { return _mapEntry; }
279 
280  // Called when the map is created.
281  virtual void OnCreate(TMap* /*map*/) { }
282 
283  // Called just before the map is destroyed.
284  virtual void OnDestroy(TMap* /*map*/) { }
285 
286  // Called when a grid map is loaded.
287  virtual void OnLoadGridMap(TMap* /*map*/, GridMap* /*gmap*/, uint32 /*gx*/, uint32 /*gy*/) { }
288 
289  // Called when a grid map is unloaded.
290  virtual void OnUnloadGridMap(TMap* /*map*/, GridMap* /*gmap*/, uint32 /*gx*/, uint32 /*gy*/) { }
291 
292  // Called when a player enters the map.
293  virtual void OnPlayerEnter(TMap* /*map*/, Player* /*player*/) { }
294 
295  // Called when a player leaves the map.
296  virtual void OnPlayerLeave(TMap* /*map*/, Player* /*player*/) { }
297 
298  // Called on every map update tick.
299  void OnUpdate(TMap* /*map*/, uint32 /*diff*/) override { }
300 };

2050 template<class TScript>
2051 class ScriptRegistry
2052 {
2053 public:
2054  typedef std::map<uint32, TScript*> ScriptMap;
2055  typedef typename ScriptMap::iterator ScriptMapIterator;
2056 
2057  typedef std::vector<TScript*> ScriptVector;
2058  typedef typename ScriptVector::iterator ScriptVectorIterator;
2059 
2060  // The actual list of scripts. This will be accessed concurrently, so it must not be modified
2061  // after server startup.
2062  static ScriptMap ScriptPointerList;
2063  // After database load scripts
2064  static ScriptVector ALScripts;
2065 
2066  static void AddScript(TScript* const script)
2067  {
2068  ASSERT(script);
2069 
2070  if (!_checkMemory(script))
2071  return;
2072 
2073  if (script->isAfterLoadScript())
2074  {
2075  ALScripts.push_back(script);
2076  }
2077  else
2078  {
2079  script->checkValidity();
2080 
2081  // We're dealing with a code-only script; just add it.
2082  ScriptPointerList[_scriptIdCounter++] = script;
2083  sScriptMgr->IncrementScriptCount();
2084  }
2085  }
2086 
2087  static void AddALScripts()
2088  {
2089  for(ScriptVectorIterator it = ALScripts.begin(); it != ALScripts.end(); ++it)
2090  {
2091  TScript* const script = *it;
2092 
2093  script->checkValidity();
2094 
2095  if (script->IsDatabaseBound())
2096  {
2097  if (!_checkMemory(script))
2098  {
2099  return;
2100  }
2101 
2102  // Get an ID for the script. An ID only exists if it's a script that is assigned in the database
2103  // through a script name (or similar).
2104  uint32 id = sObjectMgr->GetScriptId(script->GetName().c_str());
2105  if (id)
2106  {
2107  // Try to find an existing script.
2108  TScript const* oldScript = nullptr;
2109  for (auto iterator = ScriptPointerList.begin(); iterator != ScriptPointerList.end(); ++iterator)
2110  {
2111  // If the script names match...
2112  if (iterator->second->GetName() == script->GetName())
2113  {
2114  // ... It exists.
2115  oldScript = iterator->second;
2116  break;
2117  }
2118  }
2119 
2120  // If the script is already assigned -> delete it!
2121  if (oldScript)
2122  {
2123  delete oldScript;
2124  }
2125 
2126  // Assign new script!
2127  ScriptPointerList[id] = script;
2128 
2129  // Increment script count only with new scripts
2130  if (!oldScript)
2131  {
2132  sScriptMgr->IncrementScriptCount();
2133  }
2134  }
2135  else
2136  {
2137  // The script uses a script name from database, but isn't assigned to anything.
2138  if (script->GetName().find("Smart") == std::string::npos)
2139  LOG_ERROR("sql.sql", "Script named '%s' is not assigned in the database.",
2140  script->GetName().c_str());
2141  }
2142  }
2143  else
2144  {
2145  // We're dealing with a code-only script; just add it.
2146  ScriptPointerList[_scriptIdCounter++] = script;
2147  sScriptMgr->IncrementScriptCount();
2148  }
2149  }
2150  }
2151 
2152  // Gets a script by its ID (assigned by ObjectMgr).
2153  static TScript* GetScriptById(uint32 id)
2154  {
2155  ScriptMapIterator it = ScriptPointerList.find(id);
2156  if (it != ScriptPointerList.end())
2157  return it->second;
2158 
2159  return nullptr;
2160  }
2161 
2162 private:
2163  // See if the script is using the same memory as another script. If this happens, it means that
2164  // someone forgot to allocate new memory for a script.
2165  static bool _checkMemory(TScript* const script)
2166  {
2167  // See if the script is using the same memory as another script. If this happens, it means that
2168  // someone forgot to allocate new memory for a script.
2169  for (ScriptMapIterator it = ScriptPointerList.begin(); it != ScriptPointerList.end(); ++it)
2170  {
2171  if (it->second == script)
2172  {
2173  LOG_ERROR("scripts", "Script '%s' has same memory pointer as '%s'.",
2174  script->GetName().c_str(), it->second->GetName().c_str());
2175 
2176  return false;
2177  }
2178  }
2179 
2180  return true;
2181  }
2182 
2183  // Counter used for code-only scripts.
2184  static uint32 _scriptIdCounter;
2185 };
